   "topic": "Febrile neutropenia - the definition cut-offs and the 'antibiotics within 60 minutes' rule (oncological emergency)",
   "subarea": "Cancer principles & screening",
   "trap": "This is the most time-critical oncology emergency and the numbers are commonly tested: NEUTROPENIA = ANC < 0.5 x10^9/L; FEVER = a single temp >= 38.3C OR >= 38.0C sustained over ~1 hour. The timing rule (eviQ): broad-spectrum IV antibiotics within 30 MINUTES if the patient is systemically compromised (hypotension, hypoxia, confusion, organ dysfunction), and within 60 MINUTES if clinically stable - take cultures but do NOT wait for results. First-line empirical agent in Australia = piperacillin-tazobactam 4.5 g IV q6h (cefepime 2 g IV q8h if penicillin issue); add vancomycin only for specific indications (line sepsis, MRSA risk, shock, mucositis).",
   "whatFirst": "Suspected febrile neutropenia -> cultures (peripheral + each lumen of any central line) + IV broad-spectrum antibiotic (within 30 min if unwell, 60 min if stable). Do NOT delay antibiotics for the FBC result or imaging. Resuscitate per sepsis.",
   "discriminator": "Don't be reassured by a normal-looking patient or absent localising signs - neutropenic patients mount little inflammatory response, so fever may be the ONLY sign. Avoid PR exams/suppositories (translocation risk). MASCC score risk-stratifies for possible oral/outpatient management - but the default for the unwell or uncertain is IV in hospital.",
   "redFlags": "Hypotension, lactate rise, altered conscious state, or rigors during line flush = septic shock - escalate, ICU review, antibiotics within 30 min.",
   "mcqTrap": "Tempting wrong answer: 'wait for the blood culture / FBC result before starting antibiotics' or 'give oral antibiotics and review tomorrow', OR quoting the fever cut-off as 38.5C - eviQ uses >=38.3C once (or >=38.0C sustained 1 h). The intervention is empirical IV broad-spectrum antibiotics, urgently.",
   "mnemonic": "38.3 + 0.5, antibiotics in 60 (or 30 if shocked) - temp 38.3C, ANC 0.5, pip-tazo fast.",
   "viva": "ISBAR out loud: 'I'm calling about a patient day 10 post-chemo, febrile at 38.6 with a neutrophil count of 0.3 - I'm treating febrile neutropenia, I've taken blood cultures and started IV piperacillin-tazobactam within the hour, and I'd like senior/oncology review and sepsis monitoring.'",
