   "subarea": "Cancer principles & screening",
   "trap": "Match the biochemistry to the tumour, not just the symptom. SCLC (small cell lung) is the classic cause of BOTH SIADH (ectopic ADH -> euvolaemic HYPOnatraemia, low serum osmolality, inappropriately high urine osmolality >100 and urine Na >30) AND ectopic ACTH (Cushing's). HYPERcalcaemia of malignancy is most often SQUAMOUS cell carcinoma (lung, head & neck) via PTHrP - with SUPPRESSED PTH (the discriminator from primary hyperparathyroidism). Lambert-Eaton myasthenic syndrome (proximal weakness that IMPROVES with repeated effort, areflexia, autonomic features) = SCLC, anti-VGCC antibodies; distinguish from myasthenia gravis which WORSENS with effort.",
   "whatFirst": "New paraneoplastic syndrome in a smoker -> investigate for an underlying (often occult) malignancy, classically SCLC. Treating the cancer treats the syndrome; the paraneoplastic effect is NOT due to local tumour spread.",
   "discriminator": "Hypercalcaemia: malignancy (PTHrP) = PTH SUPPRESSED, often acute/symptomatic, high calcium; primary hyperparathyroidism = PTH high/inappropriately normal, chronic, milder. SIADH = euvolaemic with concentrated urine despite hyponatraemia; differentiate from hypovolaemic (dry, urine Na <20) and hypervolaemic (oedema) hyponatraemia. LEMS improves with use; MG fatigues with use.",
